SIMPLE: obvious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obvious
<hw>Ob"vi*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obvius</ets>; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>via</ets>
way. See <er>Voyage</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Opposing;
fronting.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the evil turn⟦br⟧
My <qex>obvious</qex> breast.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exposed; subject; open; liable.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Obvious</xex> to dispute.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Easily discovered, seen, or understood; readily
perceived by the eye or the intellect; plain; evident; apparent; <as>as,
an <ex>obvious</ex> meaning; an <ex>obvious</ex> remark.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Apart and easy to be known they lie,⟦br⟧
Amidst the heap, and <qex>obvious</qex> to the eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Plain; clear; evident. See
<er>Manifest</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ob"vi*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ob"vi*ous-ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obvoluted</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Obvolute</ent>⟦br⟧
